{"commentCount":2,"lastActivityDate":"2014-05-28 05:47:46.92","ownerUserId":"645","body":"&lt;p&gt;The proper translation of the verb &quot;to issue&quot; is &quot;rilasciare&quot;, so you would say:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Devo farmi rilasciare una nuova carta d'identità&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;However, commonly you would use the active form, saying, for example:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Devo richiedere una nuova carta di identità&quot; (formal)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;or just:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Devo rifare la carta di identità&quot; (informal and normally used while speaking)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Rifare&quot; is a verb which is mostly used in informal contexts and which means &quot;fare di nuovo&quot; (to do again).&lt;/p&gt;","score":6,"creationDate":"2014-05-27 19:11:03.963","title":"","tags":"","postTypeId":2,"id":1979}
